# ── Client (Vite) — safe to commit; values are inlined into the static bundle.
# Never put API secrets in VITE_* variables.
#
# Dev (this file, copied to `.env`): use a relative path. Vite's `server.proxy`
# in `vite.config.ts` forwards `/api/ai/chat` to the local wrangler dev server
# on :8787, keeping the client URL identical to true same-origin deployments.
#
# Production: when the static site is served from a host that CAN route to
# the Worker (Cloudflare Pages, or a zone with `/api/*` → this Worker), keep
# the relative path in `.env.production`. When served from GitHub Pages (no
# path-level routing to Workers is possible on `*.github.io`), `.env.production`
# must point at the absolute Worker URL so the browser calls it cross-origin.
# See the committed `.env.production` and `README.md` § AI Dialogue Proxy.
VITE_AI_PROXY_URL=/api/ai/chat
VITE_AI_PRIMARY=deepseek
VITE_AI_FALLBACK=openai

# ── Cloudflare Worker (proxy/) — set via `wrangler secret put` or dashboard.
# Never commit real keys. Local dev: copy to proxy/.dev.vars (gitignored).
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-chat
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4.1-mini
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:5173,https://manu72.github.io
